						<summary>

						<p>This is fragmentary. This seems to record a royal order issued through (the officer) Kurukulattaraiyaṉ to the residents of Kariyadēvanallūr conferring certain social privileges on them like construction of double-storied houses, sounding of drums on occasions auspicious and otherwise and some others the nature of which is not clear.</p>						

						</summary>
